    <div class="content-ul">
      <ol>
        <li>What is membership?
          <p>
              Membership is one of the premium product of Nyaya Portal for promoting arbitration among the commerce sector. Membership can be bought by business entity whether big or small. By purchasing membership business entities agree to incorporate National Arbitral Tribunal’s arbitration clause in their routine business documents for the future dispute resolution. Nyaya Portal’s membership holder can access the institution arbitration facilities and re solve their commercial disputes at a very low cost without going the court of law.
          </p>
        </li>
        
        
        <li>What is the cost of Nyaya Portal’s Membership?
          <p>
              Membership is based on turnover of the businesses. Membership can be bought by businesses with a minimum annual turnover of Rs. 20, 00,000 and above. Membership prices vary between the ranges of Rs.10,000 to Rs. 125,000 depending upon the annual business turnover of the client with a one-time registration fee of Rs. 5000.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>What are the benefits of Nyaya Portal’s Membership?
          <p>
              Membership holders are given huge exemption in the arbitration fees mentioned in the Schedule-I of National Arbitral Tribunal (Procedural) Rules. The exemptions in fee depends upon the sum in dispute or claim value. In some cases the exemptions are up to 50%. These exemptions can be availed by the membership holder during the valid period of Membership on any number of cases.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>What is the most important thing that needs to be followed by the Membership Holder?
          <p>
              The membership holder need to follow the provisions mentioned under Section 7 of Arbitration and Conciliation Act, 1996. These provisions can be followed by the Membership holder by either using the National Arbitral Tribunal’s arbitration clause in their contractual agreements and in case of non – contractual business transactions by simply asking the party with whom they are doing business to sign the ‘Consent letter’. The membership holder needs to keep the original copy of the above-mentioned document safely.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>How can I issue membership to the client?
          <p>
              Membership can be issued to the clients only through the professionals. To issue the membership you need to login to your account, and click on the ‘membership’ button on the side panel of the dashboard, then click on the sub option ‘issue membership’. On doing so, a page will open with a form. Fill the form carefully with all the details, review the entered data, make payment and proceed to get Membership card and invoice, both membership card and invoice can be downloaded.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>What are the documents required to create a Membership?
          <p>
              For creating a membership, you need client’s business’s Pan Card Number, GST registration number, and the details of the Authority on behalf of the business entity.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>What will happen after making the payment for Membership?
          <p>
              After making the payment you will get an option to download the membership card which will have all the necessary details of the beneficiary of the particular membership along with the “Model Arbitration clause/Consent letter”, after downloading the membership card you can also download the invoice.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>Can a client purchase a membership directly on the portal?
          <p>
              No, the client cannot purchase a membership directly on the portal, it can be purchased only through a professional. 
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>How can the Membership holder submit a claim?
          <p>
              The membership holder can submit the claim through a professional by verifying the membership and submitting the claim online through Nyaya Portal’s homepage with the documents required as per Section 7 of Arbitration and Conciliation Act,1996.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>How is an award obtained through arbitration is enforced?
          <p>
              According to section 36(1) Arbitration and Conciliation (Amended) Act, 2015, the award shall be enforced in accordance with the Code of Civil Procedural, 1908, in the same manner as if it were a decree of the court.
          </p>
        </li>
        
      </ol>
    </div>
